The paper proposes a novel framework for image compression using multiple description coding (MDC) and convolutional neural networks (CNNs). The main focus is on generating appearance-similar yet feature-different multiple descriptions of an image using a multiple description generator network (MDGN) based on image context features. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves compression and transmission of data, which could fall under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of neural networks for compression also suggests that the paper could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves objective and subjective quality measurements, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
